commentTextItems.html: full volley outside off-stump, Barresi angles the bat away and it runs away behind third man for four runs

commentPostTextItems.html: The Netherlands win by 6 wickets with an over and a ball to spare, and they made it look comfortable too, with Zuiderent and Barresi seeing the Dutch home. Bangladesh batting well in the first 15 overs but then crumbled to an average score which they would have still fancied to defend. They had their own fair share of chances, with some dropped catches and horrible mis-fields but credit to the Netherlands batsmen who didn't succumb to the pressure of a collapse.

This victory also qualifies the Netherlands for the ICC ODI ranking table, along with other associates Ireland and Kenya. Bangladesh will be disappointed after loosing to Ireland last week as well as they struggle to establish the gap between them and the associate nations. However, I think the victory has to go to the Netherlands, rather than Bangladesh loosing the game.
Thanks for joining here at Cricinfo today and we hope you have enjoyed today's commentary of the ODI between Netherlands and Bangladesh at Titwood in Glasgow. Have a good evening.

commentTextItems.html: cut away in front of point and they take two quickly
fuller length and he can only dig away the yorker
hit hard through midwicket, beats the close fielders and races away for four
blocked back to the bowler, good length
great diving stop in the covers from the captain Masrafe

commentTextItems.html: cut in to the ground towards cover
flicked in the gap at midwicket and quick running for the second
drives down the ground to long-on
reverse sweep, making them pay for the mistake, floats over short fine leg and away for four

missed run out, shocking fielding from Bangladesh as a mix-up between both batsmen leaves them stranded in the middle, Masrafe picks up the ball and throws it to Musfiqur who can't gather the ball, it bounces away and Netherlands get away with it

commentPostTextItems.html: All the Bangladesh fielders have their heads in their hands now, that was a great chance. All he needed was a simple lob to the keeper

commentTextItems.html: another single to the fielder and quick running again
